</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usomberlainwayfaerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Somberlain Wayfaerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(1/24/02 11:34:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Look at it like this...</span><hr size=1> The message boards, reservations boards and actual guilds themselves are created BY the players FOR the players.  Hosting, maintenance, patching and customer service are handled by Verant and/or Sony, but the day-to-day events that go on are all as a result of the actions of individual players.  For many of those players, being in a guild like Vindication or Hoss represents the pinnacle of achievement in EverQuest, because they are playing with players who put the same amount of time and effort into the game, which in turn means being able to enjoy parts of the game that most players will never experience.<br>
<br>
Is Vindication preventing people from enjoying parts of the game?  Yes, a small percentage of players in the &quot;same league&quot; as Vindication.  By releasing the Sleeper, did Hoss prevent other people from enjoying parts of the game?  Yep, drops from a few mobs in a single zone that happen to represent some of the best loot in the game.<br>
<br>
A few players did what they wanted to do, and selfish as it was, they are allowed to do it as far as the rules are concerned.  It's all about a &quot;show of force&quot;, getting enough people together in one place at one time, and doing whatever the heck you want.  Whether it's right or wrong depends on whether you look at it from an official rules-based standpoint or as part of the player community.  As a player, it sucks that other players would do the things that have been done, but when you don't NEED anyone but your own guild to enjoy the game, does it matter any more?  <br>
<br>
If you are really feeling ripped off by Vindication or Hoss or anyone else, I guess you're entitled to complain.  Try to out-screw each other until people start getting banned.  But I have this feeling that a lot of the complaining is being done by a good number of people who never would have cared in the first place if someone hadn't decided to bring the whole topic up here.  And there are probably a fair number of hypocrites too, who would have done EXACTLY the same thing if they actually had the means at their disposal to do it.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Nice guys finish last?  Why do nice guys want to be in the race anyway?&quot;<br>
<br>
